Music star Adekunle Gold has said that he might write a song for his favourite football club, Manchester United. The hit maker made this known in a recent interview with the club published on their official site. When asked if he would write a song about popular British football club, he responded: “I just might! When we win the league then I’ll be in touch.” Sharing what started his passion and support for the club, the ‘High’ singer said: “Around the 2006/07 season, myy friends always used to talk about Manchester United but I never really understood the hype because I wasn’t really into football that much back then. - Advertisement - “And then, all of a sudden I realised it was actually a really cool thing to watch! I first got exposed to the game when Ronaldo was first here and it was the era of him and Tevez et cetera. It was a great introduction into the club for me.”   Nine things you probably shouldn’t do on…     Kate Henshaw shares throwback photos, gushes for ageless…     Why I want to travel the world – Regina Daniels   However speaking on what the club means to him, he said: “Everything. If you follow me, you’ll know that I might not always be active on social media. “But as soon as it’s football time, Manchester United time, I’m there watching the football and tweeting about United!” Revealing his favorite United player of all time, he said “Cristiano Ronaldo! We have different names for him, you see. Back home in Nigeria, we call him Ororo, which is a sweet and smooth groundnut oil, and of course, he is sweet and smooth. Of all time, it’s definitely Cristiano Ronaldo!” Adekunle Gold further noted how his passion for the club influenced his latest album. He said: “I’ve been a fan for so long, you know? I’ve been there through the losses but I just love this club so much. ” It’s the tenacity and resilience that the club shows. Everybody gets sad and has downtimes in football but I’m passionate about this club, and I have the same attitude in my music!”